food, and more \\u2014 and in the process get muddy, wet, and dirty wild exploring their connection to nature.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\t<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/hands-on-nature-anarchy-zone\\/\\\">Visit the Hand on Nature Anarchy Zone<\\/a>.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tFlowing from Gaia\'s natural wetlands habitat, bird habitat garden and wildflower meadow at the south end, through an Ecological Edible Garden and urban agriculture center to the north meadow, the Ithaca Children\'s Garden is ever growing. Visit early and often and take part in community events based on nature, and the land.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tPlanning a visit to Ithaca Children\'s Garden? Check out our programs and events, or drop us a line and let us know how we can help. Visited the garden recently, or have a memory you\'d like to share? <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/contact\\/\\\">Contact us<\\/a>, or post on our <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/ithacachildrensgarden\\\">Facebook page<\\/a>!\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n\\tICG is a grassroots organization, and relies on support from many community partners including individuals, families, businesses and organizations\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}},\"59\":{\"143\":{\"type\":\"sidebarBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>The Master Plan<\\/h2><p>Check out our project page to see what is in the works for future development at the Garden. Projects currently being developed include the Bulb Labyrinth Memorial Garden, Perimeter Fence, Hands-On Nature Anarchy Zone, and Carbon-neutral eco-Education Building.<\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2015-01-11 16:57:01', '2015-01-11 16:57:01', '4cc1bfdc-2a8d-4c06-903c-6291d5706965');
INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `num`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('108', '144', '9', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone\",\"slug\":\"hands-on-nature-anarchy-zone\",\"postDate\":1420995690,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"38\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>We all know that children need fun opportunities to get outside and connect with nature in hands-on and bodies-on ways using all their senses, but did you know that children who play outside are more likely to become adults who care about the environment? ICG\'s mission is to cultivate environmental stewardship, and we believe the best way to do that is getting kids outside, having fun in the natural world.<\\/p><p>The Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone invites visitors to take it to the next level and dig for worms, play with water sand and clay, build forts out of straw bales and stumps, climb trees, and more \\u2014 and in the process get muddy, wet, and dirty while exploring their connection to nature. <\\/p><p>A lockable storage shed houses tools and materials to be used during each program. Locust logs, straw bales, topsoil, river clay, cardboard, sand, boulders, etc. invite children to play, create, destruct, work together, work alone, solve problems, and have fun.<\\/p><p>Get ready for a playful summer at ICG\'s Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone! Three weeks of<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/summer-camp-2014\\\">Nature Play Corp Summer Camp<\\/a>, trained playworkers, special Thursday morning <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/zone-into-nature\\\">Zone into Nature program<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/adventure-play-days\\\">Adventure Play Days<\\/a>, local artists and build leaders, all come together in the Anarchy Zone to help provide your child with one of the most essential ingredients of a healthy childhood: child-directed free play. <\\/p><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=ppc3bcGyd9s&amp;list=UUim9TnNKH5yinZm8_L95C-A\\\">Featured on the Katie Couric show<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npr.org\\/blogs\\/ed\\/2014\\/08\\/04\\/334896321\\/where-the-wild-things-play\\\">recognized on NPR,<\\/a> the Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone integrates models of nature play + adventure playgrounds + city farms from Germany, Scandinavia, and the UK, and works with international play experts to train our playworkers. Ithaca Children\'s Garden is the first example in the US of integrating Playwork and nature-based learning into a children\'s garden setting.<\\/p><p>Seed funding was provided by US Fish &amp; Wildlife Service (USFWS) in 2012, and 2013. 2014 funding was provided by USFWS and Park Foundation.<\\/p><p>In partnership with <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/rustykeeler.com\\/\\\">Rusty Keeler<\\/a> of <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/earthplay.net\\/\\\">EarthPlay<\\/a>. <\\/p><p>International Mud Day and the Festival of Fire &amp; Ice are Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone events funded with grants by the Tompkins County Tourism Program.<\\/p>\"}}},\"59\":\"\"}}', '2015-01-11 17:01:30', '2015-01-11 17:01:30', '4b1c5c6c-a3bb-4274-a294-052f8be516a9');
INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `num`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('109', '144', '9', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone\",\"slug\":\"hands-on-nature-anarchy-zone\",\"postDate\":1420995660,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"38\":{\"145\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>We all know that children need fun opportunities to get outside and connect with nature in hands-on and bodies-on ways using all their senses, but did you know that children who play outside are more likely to become adults who care about the environment? ICG\'s mission is to cultivate environmental stewardship, and we believe the best way to do that is getting kids outside, having fun in the natural world.<\\/p><p>The Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone invites visitors to take it to the next level and dig for worms, play with water sand and clay, build forts out of straw bales and stumps, climb trees, and more \\u2014 and in the process get muddy, wet, and dirty while exploring their connection to nature. <\\/p><p>A lockable storage shed houses tools and materials to be used during each program. Locust logs, straw bales, topsoil, river clay, cardboard, sand, boulders, etc. invite children to play, create, destruct, work together, work alone, solve problems, and have fun.<\\/p><p>Get ready for a playful summer at ICG\'s Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone! Three weeks of<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/summer-camp-2014\\\">Nature Play Corp Summer Camp<\\/a>, trained playworkers, special Thursday morning <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/zone-into-nature\\\">Zone into Nature program<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/adventure-play-days\\\">Adventure Play Days<\\/a>, local artists and build leaders, all come together in the Anarchy Zone to help provide your child with one of the most essential ingredients of a healthy childhood: child-directed free play. <\\/p><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=ppc3bcGyd9s&amp;list=UUim9TnNKH5yinZm8_L95C-A\\\">Featured on the Katie Couric show<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npr.org\\/blogs\\/ed\\/2014\\/08\\/04\\/334896321\\/where-the-wild-things-play\\\">recognized on NPR,<\\/a> the Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone integrates models of nature play + adventure playgrounds + city farms from Germany, Scandinavia, and the UK, and works with international play experts to train our playworkers. Ithaca Children\'s Garden is the first example in the US of integrating Playwork and nature-based learning into a children\'s garden setting.<\\/p><p>Seed funding was provided by US Fish &amp; Wildlife Service (USFWS) in 2012, and 2013. 2014 funding was provided by USFWS and Park Foundation.<\\/p><p>In partnership with <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/rustykeeler.com\\/\\\">Rusty Keeler<\\/a> of <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/earthplay.net\\/\\\">EarthPlay<\\/a>. <\\/p><p>International Mud Day and the Festival of Fire &amp; Ice are Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone events funded with grants by the Tompkins County Tourism Program.<\\/p>\"}}},\"59\":\"\"}}', '2015-01-11 17:07:02', '2015-01-11 17:07:02', '1ccf3537-32b6-45d1-b102-7073c8e302d4');
INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` (`id`, `entryId`, `sectionId`, `creatorId`, `locale`, `num`, `notes`, `data`, `dateCreated`, `dateUpdated`, `uid`) VALUES ('110', '144', '9', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"11\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone\",\"slug\":\"hands-on-nature-anarchy-zone\",\"postDate\":1420995660,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"38\":{\"145\":{\"type\":\"textBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>We all know that children need fun opportunities to get outside and connect with nature in hands-on and bodies-on ways using all their senses, but did you know that children who play outside are more likely to become adults who care about the environment? ICG\'s mission is to cultivate environmental stewardship, and we believe the best way to do that is getting kids outside, having fun in the natural world.<\\/p><p>The Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone invites visitors to take it to the next level and dig for worms, play with water sand and clay, build forts out of straw bales and stumps, climb trees, and more \\u2014 and in the process get muddy, wet, and dirty while exploring their connection to nature. <\\/p><p>A lockable storage shed houses tools and materials to be used during each program. Locust logs, straw bales, topsoil, river clay, cardboard, sand, boulders, etc. invite children to play, create, destruct, work together, work alone, solve problems, and have fun.<\\/p><p>Get ready for a playful summer at ICG\'s Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone! Three weeks of<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/summer-camp-2014\\\">Nature Play Corp Summer Camp<\\/a>, trained playworkers, special Thursday morning <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/zone-into-nature\\\">Zone into Nature program<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ithacachildrensgarden.org\\/index.php\\/programs\\/read\\/adventure-play-days\\\">Adventure Play Days<\\/a>, local artists and build leaders, all come together in the Anarchy Zone to help provide your child with one of the most essential ingredients of a healthy childhood: child-directed free play. <\\/p><p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=ppc3bcGyd9s&amp;list=UUim9TnNKH5yinZm8_L95C-A\\\">Featured on the Katie Couric show<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npr.org\\/blogs\\/ed\\/2014\\/08\\/04\\/334896321\\/where-the-wild-things-play\\\">recognized on NPR,<\\/a> the Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone integrates models of nature play + adventure playgrounds + city farms from Germany, Scandinavia, and the UK, and works with international play experts to train our playworkers. Ithaca Children\'s Garden is the first example in the US of integrating Playwork and nature-based learning into a children\'s garden setting.<\\/p><p>Seed funding was provided by US Fish &amp; Wildlife Service (USFWS) in 2012, and 2013. 2014 funding was provided by USFWS and Park Foundation.<\\/p><p>In partnership with <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/rustykeeler.com\\/\\\">Rusty Keeler<\\/a> of <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/earthplay.net\\/\\\">EarthPlay<\\/a>. <\\/p><p>International Mud Day and the Festival of Fire &amp; Ice are Hands-on-Nature Anarchy Zone events funded with grants by the Tompkins County Tourism Program.<\\/p>\"}}},\"59\":\"\"}}', '2015-01-11 17:07:03', '2015-01-11 17:07:03', 'e35e08b9-009d-47d6-b5e6-4400eccda886');
