INSERT INTO `craft_searchindex` (`elementId`, `attribute`, `fieldId`, `locale`, `keywords`) VALUES ('138', 'field', '38', 'en_us', ' ithaca children s garden is a very special place designed and developed in harmony with the natural and cultural landscape of the region the ithaca children s garden is uniquely ithaca built by and for the community using local materials designers and artisans you won t find a garden like it elsewhere ithaca is obviously a beautiful place and children have a lot of access to wonderful parts of nature here says rusty keeler author of natural playscapes father and owner of earthplay but the children s garden is the one place that says this is for kids it s a place that belongs to kids a place to grow up in bulb labyrinth memorial garden bulbs symbolize hope and the cycle of life labyrinths have been used for centuries by many cultures around the world to promote healing and meditation the garden is designed to be a beautiful uplifting sensory garden that celebrates the natural rhythms of the seasons hands on nature anarchy zone we all know that children need fun opportunities to get outside and connect with nature in hands on and bodies on ways using all their senses the hands on anarchy zone invites visitors to take it to the next level and dig for worms play with water sand and clay plant trees build forts out of straw bales and stumps cook food and more and in the process get muddy wet and dirty wild exploring their connection to nature visit the hand on nature anarchy zone flowing from gaia s natural wetlands habitat bird habitat garden and wildflower meadow at the south end through an ecological edible garden and urban agriculture center to the north meadow the ithaca children s garden is ever growing visit early and often and take part in community events based on nature and the land planning a visit to ithaca children s garden check out our programs and events or drop us a line and let us know how we can help visited the garden recently or have a memory you d like to share contact us or post on our facebook page icg is a grassroots organization and relies on support from many community partners including individuals families businesses and organizations ');
